id_rsa_homework.pub:
ssh-rsa  matthew@codename-bravo

=======Private Key========

We can expect the private key to contain this information:

   o  version is the version number of the key, which should be 0 for two-prime or 1 for multi-prime
   o  modulus is the RSA modulus n.
   o  publicExponent is the RSA public exponent e.
   o  privateExponent is the RSA private exponent d.
   o  prime1 is the prime factor p of n.
   o  prime2 is the prime factor q of n.
   o  exponent1 is d mod (p - 1).
   o  exponent2 is d mod (q - 1).
   o  coefficient is the CRT coefficient q^(-1) mod p.

To decode the private key file, I copied its contents above to https://lapo.it/asn1js/ and it gave me:

version = 0
modulus = 
publicExponent = 65537
privateExponent = 
prime1 = 
prime2 = 
exponent1 = 
exponent2 = 
coefficient = 

========Public Key========

We can expect the public key to contain this information:

   o  modulus is the RSA modulus n.
   o  publicExponent is the RSA public exponent e.

To decode the public key file, I used Choice #1 atr the bottom of the assignment page, and fed it into http://ldh.org/asn1.html, which gave me:

modulus = 
publicExponent = 65537

========Sanity Check========

To make sure these keys actually made sense, I checked some calculations, using Mathematica. According to RFC 8017:
privateExponent mod (prime1 - 1) should be exponent1, which it was.
privateExponent mod (prime2 - 1) should be exponent2, which it was.
prime1 * prime2 should be modulus, which it was.
